Some 20 people went missing while rescuers are continuing the searching work.
The fire broke out at 12:18 in the early afternoon at the refinery located in Contra Costa County east of San Francisco.
The latest torrent of snow smashed into the town of Valzur, where two people were killed and two survivors were pulled from the snow and debris.
